Jacob Zuma stepped down as the country’s president following his recall by the ANC NEC. CAPE TOWN - President Cyril Ramaphosa has hosted a Cabinet farewell cocktail in honour of former president Jacob Zuma. The event was held at Tuynhuys in Cape Town on Tuesday. Ministers and deputy ministers also attended the event. Pictures of Zuma and Ramaphosa laughing at the event were posted on Twitter. Zuma stepped down as the country’s president following his recall by the ANC NEC.   Ramaphosa, earlier on Tuesday, delivered his response to the State of the Nation Address in Parliament.